<h3>Future Technology</h3>
<div>
<p>What course is wired internet technology currently heading in? Partnership. With the development of wireless network technology, many businesses in the telecoms sector are starting to take an integrated approach to the future of wired internet technology. The following are some of the most recent technologies that mix wired and wireless features:</p>
</div>
 <div class="event">
<h3>Fi-WI</h3>
<div>

<p>FiWi
Businesses intend to combine wired and wireless technology through fiber-wireless (FiWi) networks. This strategy combines the distinct advantages of the two technologies, such as the speed of wired networks and the convenience of wireless ones, in addition to preventing a gap between them.</p>
  </div>
<div class="images">
 <img src="C:\Users\yuvra\OneDrive\Desktop\7.jfif">
 </div>
 <div class="event">
<h3>DAS</h3>
<div>
<p>DAS
Broadband wireless access is offered via Distributed Antenna Systems (DAS), which use radio-over-fiber (RoF) networks. The system works on the principle that optical signals are received by a centre unit, which remote antenna units connect to through optical fibre. The antennas then pick them up and convert them without further processing.</p>
</div>
<div class="images">
 <img src="C:\Users\yuvra\OneDrive\Desktop\8.jfif">
 </div>
